<paragraph id="8BFC8368FFEEEC18FF27EE77FE89FBDF" blockId="15.[189,334,1030,1056]" box="[189,334,1030,1056]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<heading id="D0B43404FFEEEC18FF27EE77FE89FBDF" bold="true" box="[189,334,1030,1056]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9375F7AFFEEEC18FF27EE77FE89FBDF" bold="true" box="[189,334,1030,1056]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC8368FFEEEC18FF27EE44FDB1FBB0" blockId="15.[189,630,1076,1103]" box="[189,630,1076,1103]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">LENGTH. Body 7.0 mm, wing 5.0 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC8368FFEEEC18FF27EE1EFD01FAC7" blockId="15.[189,1399,1134,1337]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
HEAD (
<figureCitation id="13789FEDFFEEEC18FE8AEE1FFEA8FB76" box="[272,367,1134,1161]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatrigon spp., head, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E–F. M.natalensissp. nov.(arrow =postocellarspot)(♁).G.M.sexmaculatus sp. nov.(♁).H. M.apiformis sp. nov. (♁). I. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). J. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). K. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). L. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). M. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀). Symbol: x = postocellar spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849882/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13789FEDFFEEEC18FE1AEE1FFE64FB76" box="[384,419,1134,1161]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[188,231,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Megatrigon spp., left antenna, lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849886/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">3B</figureCitation>
). Lateral margins of face more parallel while in 
<taxonomicName id="4C43F8EBFFEEEC18FC6EEE1EFB56FB77" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[1012,1169,1135,1160]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9375F7AFFEEEC18FC6EEE1EFB56FB77" box="[1012,1169,1135,1160]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A204E201FFEEEC18FB00EE1FFAD9FB77" box="[1178,1310,1134,1160]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
slightly divergent; distance between eyes larger than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C43F8EBFFEEEC18FD74EEE3FC4FFB54" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[750,904,1170,1195]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9375F7AFFEEEC18FD74EEE3FC4FFB54" box="[750,904,1170,1195]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A204E201FFEEEC18FC0AEEE0FBD3FB53" box="[912,1044,1169,1196]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 0.19 × width of head; ocellar triangle eqilateral, without median longitudinal groove; on face microtrichiose stripes along eye margin wide at the level of antennae, but tapering and reduced at lower part, connected with microtrichia below antenna by tiny oblique microtrichiose line; median facial stripe well developed; microtrichia on postocular orbit do not exceed post-ocular ridge.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC8368FFEEEC18FF27EF28FD77FA47" blockId="15.[189,1399,1368,1465]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">THORAX. Mesoscutum with two lateral microtrichiose stripes and two submedian microtrichiose stripes ending well behind level of transverse suture; supra-alar setae yellow; microtrichia on mediotergite medially occupied more than 0.5 of width.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC8368FFEEEC18FF27EFA8FD02F9E9" blockId="15.[189,1399,1496,1558]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">WING. Membrane not infuscated, with light brown veins, microtrichia brown; cell br above vena spuria narrowly bare; costagium with yellow setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC8368FFEEEC18FF27EC47FCE0F98C" blockId="15.[189,1398,1589,1651]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
LEGS (
<figureCitation id="13789FEDFFEEEC18FE9CEC44FE8DF9B0" box="[262,330,1589,1616]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,1586,1896]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,1586,1898]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 6. Megatrigon spp., metafemur, ♁ (SEM). A. Megatrigon argentifrons sp. nov., proximal half posterodorsally with striae (arrow). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov., enlarged striae. C. M. magnicornis sp. nov., anteroventral preapical flange." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849898" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849898/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
A–B). Setae on legs white without black ones; tarsomere 1 of metatarsus darkened dorsally, but without black setae intermingled with light ones.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFC8368FFEEEC18FF27ECE2FB87F87F" blockId="15.[189,1399,1682,1920]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
ABDOMEN (
<figureCitation id="13789FEDFFEEEC18FEA7ECE3FE5CF952" box="[317,411,1682,1709]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[241,1346,265,1784]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 1. Megatrigon spp., habitus, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849878/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 1B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13789FEDFFEEEC18FE30ECE2FE0BF952" box="[426,460,1683,1709]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1862,1888]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Megatrigon spp., abdomen, dorsal view, ♁. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849902/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">7B</figureCitation>
). Tergites 2+3 with large silver spots, touching lateral and posterior margins of tergites, and almost anterior corner; tergite 3 is 2.2 × as wide as long (wider than in the closely related species 
<taxonomicName id="4C43F8EBFFEEEC18FE82ECABFE71F90C" authority="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape, 2016" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" box="[280,438,1753,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natalensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9375F7AFFEEEC18FE82ECABFE71F90C" box="[280,438,1753,1779]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A204E201FFEEEC18FE27ECA8FDDCF90C" box="[445,539,1753,1779]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); distance between silver spots on tergite 3 large, 0.22 × as wide as tergite (larger than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C43F8EBFFEEEC18FEF7EC8CFDCAF8E9" authority="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape, 2016" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" box="[365,525,1788,1814]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natalensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9375F7AFFEEEC18FEF7EC8CFDCAF8E9" box="[365,525,1788,1814]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A204E201FFEEEC18FD8FEC8CFDB2F8E8" box="[533,629,1789,1815]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); tergites, especially black parts (median part of tergites 2+3 and whole tergite 4) covered with short, adpressed white-yellow setae (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C43F8EBFFEEEC18FC6BED51FB57F8C6" authority="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape, 2016" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" box="[1009,1168,1823,1849]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natalensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9375F7AFFEEEC18FC6BED51FB57F8C6" box="[1009,1168,1823,1849]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A204E201FFEEEC18FB0DED51FB35F8C5" box="[1175,1266,1824,1850]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
longer and intensively yellow); silver spots on tergite 3 with reduced setae (contrary to 
<taxonomicName id="4C43F8EBFFEEEC18FBC6ED32FB3AF8A3" authority="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape, 2016" authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" box="[1116,1277,1858,1884]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natalensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9375F7AFFEEEC18FBC6ED32FB3AF8A3" box="[1116,1277,1858,1884]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M. natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A204E201FFEEEC18FA9DED32FAAEF8A2" box="[1287,1385,1859,1885]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); tergite 4 without microtrichiose spots. Male genitalia in 
<figureCitation id="13789FEDFFEEEC18FCCAED17FC7BF87F" box="[848,956,1894,1920]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1825,1851]" captionTargetBox="[216,1374,263,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[216,1374,263,1796]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 10. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, epandrium, left lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. Megatrigon sp. from sexfasciatus group. M. M. nivalis. Symbols: x = ventral margin of median surstyle; y = posterior surstyle; z = cercus; w = subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849914" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849914/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 10B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13789FEDFFEEEC18FC53ED17FC3CF87F" box="[969,1019,1894,1920]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1758,1784]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,340,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1399,340,1716]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, hypandrium (A–M) and phallus (N), left lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. sp. from sexfasciatus group. M–N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. Symbol: x = hamus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849918/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">11B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13789FEDFFEEEC18FB9DED17FBFBF87F" box="[1031,1084,1894,1920]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,232,1794,1820]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,442,1753]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[189,1399,442,1753]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 12. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, hypandrium, ventral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. apiformis sp. nov. G. M. cooksoni sp. nov. H. M. immaculatus sp. nov. I. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. J. M. tabanoides sp. nov. K. Megatrigon sp. from the sexfasciatus group. L. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. Symbol: x = lateral ‘shoulders’." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849922" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849922/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">12B</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
